    <us-gaap:LongTermDebtTextBlock contextRef="c-1" id="f-691">Long-term Debt&lt;div style="margin-bottom:3pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:27pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"&gt;The carrying amount of our long-term debt in the form of fixed-rate senior unsecured notes (the Notes) was $28.83&#160;billion as of June&#160;30, 2025 and December&#160;31, 2024. The total estimated fair value of our outstanding Notes was $28.21&#160;billion and $27.83 billion as of June&#160;30, 2025 and December&#160;31, 2024, respectively. The fair value was determined based on the quoted prices for the Notes as of each reporting date, and is categorized accordingly as Level&#160;2 in the fair value hierarchy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</us-gaap:LongTermDebtTextBlock>
